76561197998780502,Recommended,297750,10406348,"Posted: 9 June, 2014",all,Rando,"For fans of CC: A Bridge Too Far this is very similar in style and play but with a few major imporvements. The way you manage your reinforcements is greatly changed. You can rename units if you like and it's easier to select and deselect your choices within a more regimental structure.The user interface is modernized allowing you to ctrl-group units and choose which elements you would like on your HUD and where you want them on screen. The graphics and soundsa are upgraded as well.Combat resolution is different. Truce is still there but there is not rout button that I've found. The games last longer and the maps feel larger. Improvements all around.Finally, the campaign map has an entire system of movement and action selection (rest, reinforce, move, attack) that helps tie the campaign together and makes the game less rail-roady."
